The problem is that the Text widget that's acting as the in-place editor is 
being disposed in its focus out callback, in JavaStepFilterPreferencePage 
#cleanupEditor.  This has always caused problems, and should not be done (see 
readme_swt, bullet 1.3).  So a change is required on your end.

This has been handled in the past simply by putting the dispose() invocation 
into a display.asyncExec runnable so that it will be executed a bit later.  ie.-

   fEditorText.getDisplay().asyncExec(new Runnable() {
      public void run() {
         fEditorText.dispose();
      }
   });

Doing so gets rid of the GP, but introduces a NullPointer on all platforms as a 
result of changing the order to execution.  So you'll need to introduce the 
above snippet AND make some subsequent changes to compensate for it.
